title: London Spy
description:
First shown through Nov/Dec 2015 on BBC TV
Ben Whishaw plays Danny, a troubled mid-twenties club goer, frustrated about his sexuality and life in general. Just as he's all but given up, he meets an average 'Joe' on the street who is out for a morning jog. This starts an elborate getting to know you process, when Joe reveals his name to be Alex and a city banker. 

However things take a turn for the sinister just as Danny finally finds happiness and must discover exactly what has happened to Alex. Who appears to have been less than truthful about who exactly he is. Further deaths, more plot twists and cliff hangers that hold the tension throughout. Danny must go through a series of events to uncover the truth, regain his freedom and sanity. How far does he need to go? Who is trying to prevent him from finding out the truth.

Ben Whishaw (Q from the James Bond movies) plays Danny, alongside an ensemble cast including Jim Broadbent, Edward Alcroft and Samantha Spiro
